  "prompt": "How long can white wine last after it has been open?",
  "response": "Once opened, white wine generally lasts for about 3 to 5 days when stored properly. To maximize its freshness, it's best to reseal the bottle with its original cork or a wine stopper and store it in the refrigerator. The cooler temperature slows down the oxidation process, helping to preserve the wine's flavor and aroma. After a few days, the wine may start to lose its quality, so it's often best to consume it within that time frame for the best taste.",
